<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="120" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1903,2039]" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1903,1930]" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Cercus caudoventrally narrow and elongated anteriad in ventral view, with ca. three black, stout, peglike spines, lacking a patch of short, thick spines (
<figureCitation box="[723,814,1940,1966]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1854,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,597,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,597,1835]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Hirtodrosophila lambda sp. nov. (holotype 06453). A, B, periphallic organs (posterior and posterolateral view, respectively); C, ventral lobe of epandrium (lateral view); D, cerci (ventral view); E, dorsal part of surstylus (posterolateral view); F, inner surface of surstylus (posterolateral view); G, H, 10th sternite (anterior and ventral view, respectively); I−K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, sensilla of paramere (ventrolateral view); M, fork of aedeagus (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415693" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415693/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
). Fork of aedeagus with branches pointed apically and broadened basally, and finely serrate on apex to lateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[862,928,1976,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1854,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,597,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,597,1835]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Hirtodrosophila lambda sp. nov. (holotype 06453). A, B, periphallic organs (posterior and posterolateral view, respectively); C, ventral lobe of epandrium (lateral view); D, cerci (ventral view); E, dorsal part of surstylus (posterolateral view); F, inner surface of surstylus (posterolateral view); G, H, 10th sternite (anterior and ventral view, respectively); I−K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, sensilla of paramere (ventrolateral view); M, fork of aedeagus (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415693" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415693/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
I–K, M).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="121" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1903,2039]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,153,1116]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="121" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,2011,2038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Description</emphasis>
(characters commonly seen in 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen &amp; Katoh &amp; Gao, 2019" authorityName="Chen &amp; Katoh &amp; Gao" authorityYear="2019" box="[687,873,2012,2038]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Hirtodrosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minshanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[687,873,2012,2038]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">H. minshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[880,969,2012,2038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[880,969,2012,2038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
not repeated) (
<specimenCount box="[1140,1163,2012,2038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
). Head (
<figureCitation box="[1258,1377,2012,2038]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1948,1973]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,669,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,669,1929]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Left lateral habitus, head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (left ventral or right dorsal view), and abdomen (dorsal view). A−D, H. minshanensis sp. nov. (holotype 06466); E−H, H. lambda sp. nov. (holotype 06453). Scale bar (dashed) = 0.5 mm (the same in the following figures)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253622/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Figs 2E, F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1388,1401,2012,2038]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,694,719]" captionTargetBox="[163,1433,181,675]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,181,675]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Head (anterior view), postocciput (posterior view), cibarium (dorsal and lateral view), and prementum (ventral and lateral view). A−F, H. minshanensis sp. nov. (paratype 06449); G−L, H. lambda sp. nov. (paratype 06455). Abbreviations: cly = clypeus, m s = medial sensilla, p s = posterior sensilla, spc s = supracervical setae. Scale bar (solid) = 0.1 mm (the same in the following figures)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415689" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415689/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">4</figureCitation>
G– L) nearly entirely blackish brown, except for red eyes. Frontal vitta and fronto-orbital plate posteriorly paler. Ocellar triangle brown along margin of triangle made by ocelli. Arista with 4–5 dorsal branches. Supracervical setae 12–13 per side; postocular setae ca. 37 per side. Cibarium with 6–7medial and ca. 19 posterior sensilla per side. Prementum with five (one proximal, two lateral, and two distal) pairs of setae. Labellum with seven pseudotracheae per side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,153,1116]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">
Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[296,413,297,324]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1948,1973]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,669,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,669,1929]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Left lateral habitus, head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (left ventral or right dorsal view), and abdomen (dorsal view). A−D, H. minshanensis sp. nov. (holotype 06466); E−H, H. lambda sp. nov. (holotype 06453). Scale bar (dashed) = 0.5 mm (the same in the following figures)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253622/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Fig. 2E, F</figureCitation>
): Postpronotal lobe dark brown, ventrally paler, with ca. three prominent setae, middle one longer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,153,1116]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">
Legs (
<figureCitation box="[269,354,369,396]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1948,1973]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,669,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,669,1929]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Left lateral habitus, head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (left ventral or right dorsal view), and abdomen (dorsal view). A−D, H. minshanensis sp. nov. (holotype 06466); E−H, H. lambda sp. nov. (holotype 06453). Scale bar (dashed) = 0.5 mm (the same in the following figures)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253622/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
) yellowish brown to dark grayish brown; foreleg darker in color than others. First tarsomeres of all legs shorter than total length of four succeeding tarsomeres.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,153,1116]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">
Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[397,469,441,468]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1854,1879]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,597,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,597,1835]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Hirtodrosophila lambda sp. nov. (holotype 06453). A, B, periphallic organs (posterior and posterolateral view, respectively); C, ventral lobe of epandrium (lateral view); D, cerci (ventral view); E, dorsal part of surstylus (posterolateral view); F, inner surface of surstylus (posterolateral view); G, H, 10th sternite (anterior and ventral view, respectively); I−K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, sensilla of paramere (ventrolateral view); M, fork of aedeagus (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415693" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415693/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
): Epandrium with ca. 25 long setae per side. Cercus ventrally concaved in posterior view, with ca. 44 setae including ventral thick ones. Surstylus with upper and lower, straight rows of ca. eight prensisetae in each; inner surface with ca. 27 setae, dorsal ones longer and trichoid-like, ventral ones shorter and thicker. Tenth sternite anteriorly broadened, anteromedially notched. Paramere with ca. three sensilla slightly shorter than paramedian setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,153,1116]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">
